{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bangladesh", "text_new": "{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Bangladesh}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2020}}\n{{ Infobox pandemic \n|name=2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bangladesh\n|map1=File:COVID-19 outbreak Bangladesh District Wise cases map.svg\n|legend1=      District-based Corona epidemiological map (as of April 13)\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n{{legend|#F39C9C|1-9 death cases}}\n|disease=[[ Coronavirus disease 2019| COVID-19]]\n|virus_strain=[[ SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Bangladesh]]\n| first_case      = [[Dhaka]]\n| arrival_date    = 8 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=8|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]]\n| tested          = 1338<ref name=\"dhakatribune-26march\"/>\n| recovery_cases  = 42<ref name=\"iedcr\"/>\n| deaths          = 46<ref name=\"iedcr\"/> \n| territories = As of April 8, there were '''1,212''' confirmed cases in '''37''' districts <!-- Please also update relevant information and references when changing the date. Do not confuse the reader --><ref>{{ cite web|url=https://iedcr.gov.bd/website/images/files/nCoV/Confirmed%20COVID-19%20cases_upto_13_April%202020.pdf| title=COVID-19 Confirmed cases in Bangladesh (up to April 13, 2020 at 8:00am)|website=ICDCR|date=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n{{legend|#ff5555|100\u2013499 confirmed cases }}\n[[Dhaka]]: 383; [[Narayangonj]]: 144\n{{legend|#ff8080|50\u201399 confirmed cases }}\n{{legend|#ffaaaa|10\u201349 confirmed cases }}\n[[Gazipur]]: 1; [[Narsingdi]]: 21; [[Madaripur]]: 1; [[Chattogram]]: 1; [[Munshiganj]]: 1; [[Kishoreganj]]: 1;\n{{legend|#ffd5d5|1\u20139 confirmed cases }} [[Cumilla]]: 1; [[Tangail]]: 1; [[Rajbari]]: 1; [[Chandpur]]: 1; [[Brahmanbaria]]: 1; [[Gaibandha]]: 1; [[Jamalpur]]: 1; [[Mymensingh]]: 1; [[Manikganj]]: 1; [[Nilphamari]]: 1; [[Sparkle]]: 1; [[Gopalganj]]: 1; [[Thakurgaon]]: 1; [[Barguna]]: 1; [[Rangpur]]: 2; [[Sherpur]]: 2; [[Rajshahi]]: 2; [[Patuakhali]]: 2; [[Barisal]]: 2; [[Sylhet]]: 1; [[Lakshmipur]]: 1; [[Cox's Bazar]]: 1; [[Chuadanga]]: 1; [[Habiganj]]: 1; [[Conjoined]]: 1; [[Moulvibazar]]: 1; [[Shariatpur]]: 1; [[Lalmonirhat]]: 1; [[Sunamganj]]: 1;<!-- Please also update relevant information and references when changing the date. Do not confuse the reader -->\n| total_ili=\n|website={{URL|corona.gov.bd}}\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Bangladesh]] on March 2020. The first three known cases were reported by the country's [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research (IEDCR)]] on 7 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-bangladesh-idUSKBN20V0FS|title=Bangladesh confirms its first three cases of coronavirus|date=2020-03-08|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-27|language=en}}</ref> As of 14 April, there are a total of 1012 confirmed cases, 42 recoveries, and 46 deaths in the country.<ref name=\"iedcr\"/><ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=http://corona.gov.bd/|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be \u0987\u09a8\u09ab\u09cb|last=Research (IEDCR)|first=Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and|website=corona.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nExperts criticised that not enough tests were conducted in the country that has a population of over 160 million.<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/29/covid-19-pandemic-testing-remains-low-despite-having-enough-kits-in-stock|title=Covid-19 pandemic: Testing remains low despite having enough kits in stock|date=2020-03-29|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=\"news.yahoo.com\">{{cite web|url=https://news.yahoo.com/massive-bangladesh-coronavirus-prayer-gathering-sparks-outcry-193538973.html|title=Massive Bangladesh coronavirus prayer gathering sparks outcry|website=news.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> Newspaper reports and social media continued to report about additional deaths of patients with COVID-19 symptoms. Some of the deceased were treated at COVID-19 isolation centres at hospitals in the districts and others were denied treatment, though no tests were conducted to confirm contagion.<ref name=\"newagebd.net\">{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103364/six-die-with-coronavirus-symptoms-no-new-case-reported-in-bangladesh|title=Six die with coronavirus symptoms, no new case reported in Bangladesh|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref> For a long time, testing was centralised to only [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research]] (IEDCR) in the capital [[Dhaka]], although patients with symptoms were reported all around the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/opinion/article/1645374/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%85%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%AC%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%A6|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8: \u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09b0 \u0985\u09ad\u09be\u09ac\u09c7 \u09ac\u09be\u09a1\u09bc\u09ac\u09c7 \u09ac\u09bf\u09aa\u09a6|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, Bangladesh declared a 10-day shut down effective from 26 March to 4 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/23/govt-offices-to-remain-closed-till-april-4|title=Coronavirus: Bangladesh declares public holiday from March 26 to April 4|date=2020-03-23|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> This was later increased to 25 April.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.omanobserver.om/bangladesh-has-extended-lockdown-by-11-days/|title=Bangladesh has extended lockdown by 11 days|date=2020-04-11|website=Oman Observer|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nA series of hotline numbers, email address and the Facebook page of the [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research]] (IEDCR) are provided for people to contact if they suspect [[COVID-19|Covid-19]] infection or need more information.<ref name=\"Corona starts\">{{cite news|author1=Kamrul Hasan; and Ashif Islam Shaon|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/dhaka/2020/03/08/iedcr-3-affected-with-coronavirus-in-bangladesh|title=First 3 cases of coronavirus confirmed in Bangladesh|date=8 March 2020|work=[[Dhaka Tribune]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308193315/https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/dhaka/2020/03/08/iedcr-3-affected-with-coronavirus-in-bangladesh|archivedate=8 March 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Background  ==\nOn 31 December 2019, China reported to the WHO cases of pneumonia with unknown causes. On 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Bangladesh medical cases chart}}\n\n=== January 2020===\nOn January 22, the authorities at [[Hazrat Shahjalal International Airport]] (HSIA) in Dhaka reported that they had put the airports on alert to prevent the spread of '''coronavirus''' in Bangladesh by screening travellers from China, where the virus had at that time infected nearly 300 people and killed six persons. The airport claimed to turn on its thermal scanner to scan passengers to detect any infection in passengers travelling from China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/post/233343|title=Screening starts at Dhaka, Ctg airports|website=Screening starts at Dhaka, Ctg airports {{!}} theindependentbd.com|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> A.H.M. Touhid-ul Ahsan, director of the main Shahjalal International Airport, said doctors at the airport would look for fevers, coughs, breathing difficulties and sore throats. The country's [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research]] were to be notified of any passengers with symptoms for further examination, he said.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Health/wireStory/countries-join-china-responding-coronavirus-68424857|title=Virus prompts temperature checks, extra cleaning at airports|last=News|first=A. B. C.|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nOn January 31, a special flight of Biman Bangladesh Airlines with special quarantine, three physicians, a nurse and required medical equipment on board flew to Wuhan, China to evacuate stranded Bangladeshi citizens.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/98179/government-sends-plane-today-to-fly-back-citizens|title=Government sends plane today to fly back citizens|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n=== February 2020===\nOn February 1, 312 Bangladeshi citizens (297 were adults and 15 children) stranded in Wuhan, China were evacuated and brought back to Bangladesh. Most of the Bangladeshis were students and PhD researchers at different universities in the Hubei province in China where their provincial government launched multiple screening tests before allowing them to get on board the plane. Majority of the evacuees were quarantined for 14 days at the Hajj Camp in Ashkona in Dhaka and some at the Combined Military Hospital before being released two weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/98297/312-bangladeshis-quarantined-in-dhaka-after-arriving-from-wuhan|title=312 Bangladeshis quarantined in Dhaka after arriving from Wuhan|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/98284/govt-brings-361-back-from-wuhan-early-saturday|title=Govt brings 361 back from Wuhan early Saturday|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> None of these returnees from Wuhan China were tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/100468/expats-asked-to-call-iedcr-if-in-difficulties|title=Expats asked to call IEDCR if in difficulties|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/100671/23-bangladeshis-flown-to-delhi-from-wuhan|title=23 Bangladeshis flown to Delhi from Wuhan|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nOn February 2, the government of Bangladesh decided to suspend on-arrival visas for Chinese visitors <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/98400/no-on-arrival-visa-for-chinese-visitors-bangladesh|title=No on-arrival visa for Chinese visitors: Bangladesh|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> The Chittagong port also announced that as a precautionary measure to prevent the spread of coronavirus from the ships that bring goods from around the world, the port health officer would examine all sailors of the ships coming from the East Asian countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/98374/chattogram-port-takes-measures-to-fight-coronavirus|title=Chattogram port takes measures to fight coronavirus|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n=== March 2020===\n\n==== March 8 ====\n\n* On 8 March, the first three coronavirus cases were confirmed.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-bangladesh-idUSKBN20V0FS|title=Bangladesh confirms its first three cases of coronavirus|date=2020-03-08|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-28|language=en}}</ref> The [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]]  director Prof. [[Meerjady Sabrina Flora]] announced at a press conference that 2 men (from Narayangonj) and 1 woman (From Madaripur) had tested positive for COVID-19. The patients were aged between 20 and 35. Of them, two men were Italy returnees and the woman was a family member of one of these two. IEDCR launched three hotlines to call up for information about Corona virus. Approximately about 111 tests were conducted in Bangladesh.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/news/avoid-public-transport-1877749 |title=IEDCR asks returnees from virus-affected countries to avoid public transport |publisher=The Daily Star |date=2020-03-08 |accessdate=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n* On the same day, Bangladesh decided\u00a0 not to hold the planned grand inauguration ceremony of the founding president [[Sheikh Mujibur Rahman]]'s birth centenary celebration programmes on March 17 to avoid public gatherings.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/101645/mujib-birth-centenary-inauguration-to-be-on-small-scale|title=Mujib birth centenary inauguration to be on small scale|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 16 ====\nOn 16 March, Flora stated that an additional 3 COVID-19 patients had been detected in Bangladesh, including 2 children.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://m.bdnews24.com/bn/detail/bangladesh/1735213|title= \u0986\u09b0\u0993 \u09e9 \u099c\u09a8 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09c7 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4|publisher= bdnews24|accessdate= 16 March 2020|date= 16 March 2020|language=bn}}</ref> Also, the Education Ministry of Bangladesh announced that it will close all educational institutions until 31 March and [[Dhaka University]] from 18 March 2020 to 28 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://m.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1645112/\u09e9\u09e7-\u09ae\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u099a-\u09aa\u09b0\u09cd\u09af\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4-\u09b6\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09be\u09a8-\u09ac\u09a8\u09cd\u09a7|title= \u09e9\u09e7 \u09ae\u09be\u09b0\u09cd\u099a \u09aa\u09b0\u09cd\u09af\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u09b6\u09bf\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a4\u09bf\u09b7\u09cd\u09a0\u09be\u09a8 \u09ac\u09a8\u09cd\u09a7|publisher= Daily Prothom Alo|accessdate= 16 March 2020|date=16 March 2020|language=bn}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url= https://unb.com.bd/m/category/bangladesh/dhaka-university-shut-down-over-coronavirus-fears/47156|title= Dhaka University shut down over coronavirus fears|publisher= UNB|accessdate= 16 March 2020|date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== March 17 ====\nOn 17 March, 2 more patients were diagnosed with coronavirus. One of them is an expatriate Bangladeshi and another one was in the institutional quarantine.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n==== March 18 ====\nOn 18 March, Bangladesh reported its first coronavirus death. The patient was aged over 70 and had various medical conditions like [[COPD]], [[diabetes]], [[hypertension]], heart problems.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-bangladesh-idUSL4N2BB384|title=Bangladesh reports first coronavirus death -officials|date=2020-03-18|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn the last 24 hours, 4 more COVID-19 patients (three male and one female) were detected  where as samples of 49 people were tested. The three males were returnees  from Italy and Kuwait while the female was a family member of a COVID-19 patient identified earlier.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/102574/first-covid-19-death-reported-in-bangladesh|title=Bangladesh confirms first coronavirus death|work=New Age|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.banglanews24.com/english/national/article/83210/Coronavirus-Bangladesh-confirms-first-death-4-new-cases|title=Coronavirus: Bangladesh confirms first death, 4 new cases|work=banglanews24.com|date=2020-03-18|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nTill date, there were a total of 341 individuals tested among whom there were 48 known positive cases, 1 reported death, and 3 recoveries.<ref name=\"thedailystar.net\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/1-dead-coronavirus-infection-1882474|title=Bangladesh reports first coronavirus death, number of active cases now 14|date=2020-03-18|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nDespite risks of spreading COVID-19, at least 25,000 [[Muslims]] joined a prayer named 'Khatme Shifa' after dawn to fight the Covid-19 pandemic, at Central Eidgah in [[Lakshmipur Sadar Upazila|Lakshmipur]]'s Raipur.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51956510|title=Mass prayer event in Bangladesh fuels virus fears|date=2020-03-19|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-30|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/current-affairs/2020/03/19/covid-19-bangladesh-restricts-all-kinds-of-gatherings|title=Covid-19: Bangladesh restricts all kinds of gatherings|date=2020-03-19|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/102644/coronavirus-25000-people-attend-lakshmipur-prayer|title=Coronavirus: 25,000 people attend Lakshmipur prayer|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=\"news.yahoo.com\"/>\n\n==== March 19 ====\n\n* As of March 19, a total of 397 individuals have been tested since January 21, 2020. Among all those tested, there was a total of 17 positive cases, 3 recoveries and 1 death. \n* In the last 24 hours, a total of 46 individuals have been tested among whom 3 (two males and one female) were newly tested positive. They are all members of the family of one Italy returnee. Of them, the men are aged 32 and 65 while the woman is 22 years old.\n* Bangladesh imposed its first lockdown at [[Shibchar]], [[Madaripur District|Madaripur]]. From 8PM, the local administration enforced a complete shutdown in Shibchar municipality and three unions of Shibchar upazila in an effort to contain the spread of coronavirus after 9 people from the area was announced to have tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1646471/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%9A%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE-%E0%A6%9A%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%A6%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%85%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A7-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%98%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9F-%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%82%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF|title=\u09b6\u09bf\u09ac\u099a\u09b0 \u099f\u09be\u09a8\u09be \u099a\u09be\u09b0 \u09a6\u09bf\u09a8 \u0985\u09ac\u09b0\u09c1\u09a6\u09cd\u09a7, \u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09be\u0998\u09be\u099f \u099c\u09a8\u09b6\u09c2\u09a8\u09cd\u09af|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://unb.com.bd/category/Bangladesh/bangladesh-sees-first-lockdown-in-madaripur/47542|title=Bangladesh sees first lockdown in Madaripur|last=Developer)|first=Md Ashequl Morsalin Ibne Kamal(Team Leader){{!}} Niloy Saha(Sr Web Developer){{!}} Shohana Afroz(Web Developer){{!}} Jobayer Hossain(Web|website=unb.com.bd|language=English|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 20 ====\n\n* As of March 20, the government press release stated that a total of 433 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 20 positive cases, 3 recoveries and 1 death.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 36 individuals have been tested among whom 3 (two males and one female) were newly tested positive.<ref name=\":0\" /> The female in her 30s and the male in his 70s had known contact with a recent returnee from abroad. The male in his 30s has history of travel in Rome and Berlin. The patient in his 70s was in the Intensive Care Unit (ICU) because of his critical condition.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/bengali/news-51972235 |title=\u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u0986\u09b0\u09cb \u09e9 \u099c\u09a8, \u098f\u0995\u099c\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u0985\u09ac\u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u09be \u0986\u09b6\u0999\u09cd\u0995\u09be\u099c\u09a8\u0995 | language=bn |date=20 March 2020 |access-date=21 March 2020 |publisher=[[BBC Bangla]]}}</ref>\n* The [[Daulatdia]] [[brothel]], one of the largest brothels in the world was ordered to shut down.<ref name=\"Daulatdia\">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-bangladesh/sex-workers-in-one-of-worlds-largest-brothel-appeal-for-funds-due-coronavirus-idUSL8N2BG6B1|title=Sex workers in one of world's largest brothel appeal for funds due coronavirus|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=23 March 2020|date= 23 March 2020}}</ref>\n*Mountaineer [[Wasfia Nazreen]], the first Bangladeshi to complete [[Seven Summits]], announced on [[Facebook]] that she was tested positive for COVID-19 in [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/online/wasfia-nazreen-tested-coronavirus-positive-in-usa-1883773|title=Wasfia Nazreen tested coronavirus positive in US|date=2020-03-21|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 21 ====\n\n* As of March 21, a total of 433 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 24 positive cases, 3 recoveries and 2 deaths.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 36 individuals have been tested among whom 4 were newly tested positive.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n*The second coronavirus death in Bangladesh was announced.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/102849/bangladesh-puts-area-in-capital-on-lockdown-after-second-coronavirus-death|title=Bangladesh puts area in capital on lockdown after second coronavirus death|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> The death of this man in his 70s is likely the first known death from community transmission since how he got infected remained unknown as he and his family did not have any history of travel abroad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103140/community-transmission-of-coronavirus-found-in-bangladesh-iedcr|title=Community transmission of coronavirus found in Bangladesh: IEDCR|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> Following his death at the nearby Delta Medical Hospital, the authorities locked down the Tolarbagh neighbourhood of Mirpur, Dhaka.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tbsnews.net/bangladesh/health/672-families-40-buildings-under-lockdown-dhaka-59323|title=672 families of 40 buildings under 'lockdown' in Dhaka|date=2020-03-21|website=The Business Standard|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 22 ====\n\n* As of March 22, a total of 564 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 27 positive cases, 5 recoveries and 2 deaths.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 65 individuals have been tested among whom 3 were newly tested positive.<ref name=\":0\" /> Among them, was a 30 year old doctor, who treated the patient who died on March 20.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://tbsnews.net/coronavirus-chronicle/coronavirus-bangladesh/delta-hospital-icu-head-tests-positive-covid-19-61573|title=Delta Hospital's ICU head tests positive with Covid-19|date=2020-03-27|website=The Business Standard|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n* [[Higher Secondary School Certificate]] (HSC exam) which was going to begin on 1 April got postponed until further notice.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1646310/\u098f\u0987\u099a\u098f\u09b8\u09b8\u09bf-\u09b8\u09ae\u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0-\u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be-\u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u0997\u09bf\u09a4 |title=\u098f\u0987\u099a\u098f\u09b8\u09b8\u09bf-\u09b8\u09ae\u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be \u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u0997\u09bf\u09a4| language=bn |date=22 March 2020 |access-date=22 March 2020 |publisher=Prothom Alo}}</ref>\n\n==== March 23 ====\n\n* As of March 23, a total of 620 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 33 positive cases, 5 recoveries and 3 deaths.<ref name=\":0\" /> Among those tested positive, 2 are under 10, 1 is between 10\u201320, 9 between 21\u201330, 9 between 31\u201340, 5 between 41\u201350, 1 between 51\u201360, and 6 are over 60. among the 33 affected people, 15 lived in Dhaka, 10 are from Madaripur, 3 from Narayanganj, 2 from Gaibandha, 1 from Comilla, 1 from Gazipur, and 1 from Chuadanga. Among them, 13 has a history from foreign travel and the rest transmitted the disease from those who traveled abroad. Among those who returned from a foreign country, 6 came from Italy, 2 from the US, 2 from the UK, 2 from European countries other than Italy, 1 from Bahrain, 1 from India, and 1 from Kuwait.<ref name=\":6\">{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1646517/%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%93-%E0%A7%AC-%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4-%E0%A6%8F%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81|title=\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u0986\u09b0\u0993 \u09ec \u099c\u09a8 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4, \u098f\u0995\u099c\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 56\u00a0 individuals were tested among whom 6 were newly tested positive.<ref name=\":0\" /> Among the 6 new cases (3 males, 3 females), one\u00a0 is a physician, two are nurses, and two recently arrived from India and Bahrain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/coronavirus-6-new-cases-detected-1-more-dead-says-iedcr-1884718|title=1 more dies of coronavirus, 6 new cases confirmed: IEDCR|publisher=[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|Daily Star]]|access-date=23 March 2020|date= 23 March 2020}}</ref>\n*The third known coronavirus-related death was announced.<ref name=\":6\"/> The deceased was a neighbor of the second person who died from Coronavirus. The two may have been infected at the same mosque in Tolarbag area, where they both regularly went for their prayers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/dhaka/2020/03/22/mp-claims-another-dead-from-coronavirus-in-mirpur|title=Another dies from coronavirus in Mirpur|date=2020-03-22|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n* The government announced the closure of\u00a0 all government and private offices from 26 March until 4 April to prevent the spread of coronavirus. Only emergency services like law enforcement and healthcare services were exempted from this announcement.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/govt-offices-closed-march-26-april-4-cabinet-secretary-1884730|title=Govt offices closed from March 26 to April 4: Cabinet secretary|publisher=Daily Star|accessdate=23 March 2020|date= 23 March 2020}}</ref> It was also announced that the armed forces will be deployed on March 24 to facilitate prevention of spread of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1646531/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B2-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8: \u0995\u09be\u09b2 \u09a8\u09be\u09ae\u099b\u09c7 \u09b8\u09b6\u09b8\u09cd\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0 \u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09bf\u09a8\u09c0|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 24 ====\n\n* As of March 24, a total of 712 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 39 positive cases, 5 recoveries and 4 deaths.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 92 individuals have been tested among whom 6 were newly tested positive. Among them, one recently returned from [[Saudi Arabia]] after completing [[Umrah]] and the other four were known to have come in contact with patients tested positive for COVID-19.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1646693/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%93-%E0%A6%8F%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4-%E0%A7%AC|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u0986\u09b0\u0993 \u098f\u0995\u099c\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1, \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09ec|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*The fourth known coronavirus-related death of a female occurred in the last 24 hours. The person was over 70. It is not known how the woman contracted the virus.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103079/another-coronavirus-infection-patient-dies-in-bangladesh|title=Another coronavirus infection patient dies in Bangladesh|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref name=\":3\" />\n* The government announced a 10-day ban on all passenger travel via water, rail, and domestic air routes from\u00a0 March 26 till April 4.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103078/govt-imposes-10-day-ban-on-public-transports-from-march-26|title=Govt imposes 10-day ban on public transports from March 26|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*The government deployed the armed forces, including police and army, to ensure that people maintain social distancing and quarantine to prevent spread of the deadly COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/soldiers-enforce-10-day-shutdown-bangladesh-slow-virus-69813017|title=Soldiers enforce 10-day shutdown in Bangladesh to slow virus|last=News|first=A. B. C.|website=ABC News|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/current-affairs/2020/03/23/coronavirus-bangladesh-to-deploy-armed-forces-on-tuesday|title=Coronavirus: Bangladesh to deploy armed forces on Tuesday|date=2020-03-23|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 25 ====\n\n* As of March 25, a total of 794 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 39 positive cases, 5 recoveries and 5 deaths.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 82 individuals have been tested among whom 0 were newly tested positive. 1 coronavirus-related death occurred in the last 24 hours.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n*The fifth known person to have died in Bangladesh due to COVID-19 was 65 years old and was a relative of another patient tested positive. The person was tested positive on March 18 and was receiving treatment in a hospital. When the patient's condition deteriorated, s/he was admitted to the Kuwait Friendship Hospital on March 21. The patient, who also had diabetes and hypertension, succumbed to death in the morning of March 25.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1646857/%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%93-%E0%A6%8F%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81-%E0%A7%A8%E0%A7%AA-%E0%A6%98%E0%A6%A3%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8|title=\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u0986\u09b0\u09c7\u0995\u099c\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1, \u09e8\u09ea \u0998\u09a3\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*All domestic flights were suspended.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1646678/%E0%A6%85%E0%A6%AD%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A3-%E0%A6%AB%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B2%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%9F-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%9C-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A4-%E0%A7%A7%E0%A7%A8%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BE-%E0%A6%A5%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A7|title=\u0985\u09ad\u09cd\u09af\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4\u09b0\u09c0\u09a3 \u09ab\u09cd\u09b2\u09be\u0987\u099f \u0986\u099c \u09b0\u09be\u09a4 \u09e7\u09e8\u099f\u09be \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u09ac\u09a8\u09cd\u09a7|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 26 ====\n\n* As of March 26, a total of 920 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 44 positive cases, 11 recoveries and 5 deaths.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 126 individuals were tested among whom 5 were newly tested positive.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\"Research IEDCR\">{{cite web|url=http://result.dpe.gov.bd/press-release|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be \u0987\u09a8\u09ab\u09cb|last=Research (IEDCR)|first=Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and|website=result.dpe.gov.bd|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> Among them, two are between 30 and 40, two between 40 and 50, and one is over 60.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1647083/%E0%A6%A8%EF%BF%BD|title=\u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u09aa\u09be\u0981\u099a \u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0\u09b0 \u099a\u09be\u09b0\u099c\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ac\u09af\u09bc\u09b8 \u09e9\u09e6 \u09a5\u09c7\u0995\u09c7 \u09eb\u09e6 \u09ac\u099b\u09b0|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> According to a newspaper report, an officer working at the Ministry of Health was one of those who tested positive.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1647122/%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A5%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%A6%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AE%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A6%BE-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F|title=\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09b8\u09cd\u09a5\u09cd\u09af\u09ae\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4\u09cd\u09b0\u09c0\u09b0 \u09a6\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4\u09b0\u09c7\u09b0 \u0995\u09b0\u09cd\u09ae\u0995\u09b0\u09cd\u09a4\u09be \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09c7 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n* Bangladesh observed its 50th Independence Day on a limited scale as the government cancelled all celebrations and mass gatherings to prevent the spread of coronavirus. To mark the day, important structures and main roads were illuminated and decorated with national flags.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103228/bangladesh-observes-independence-day-without-celebrations|title=Bangladesh observes Independence Day without celebrations|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n* This was the first day of the 10-day shutdown that the government announced to contain the spread of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2020/03/25/bangladesh-in-virtual-lockdown-as-coronavirus-fight-flares|title=Bangladesh in virtual lockdown as coronavirus fight flares|last=Correspondent|first=Senior|last2=bdnews24.com|website=bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103219/dhaka-wears-deserted-look-as-10-day-holiday-begins|title=Dhaka wears deserted look as 10-day holiday begins|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 27 ====\n\n* As of March 27, a total of 1026 individuals have been tested among which there is a total of 48 positive cases, 11 recoveries and 5 deaths.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* According to the government press release, in the last 24 hours, a total of 106 individuals were tested among whom 4 were newly tested positive.<ref name=\":0\" /> Among the 4 new cases (three females and one male), two are physicians who treated patients infected with COVID-19. Two are from Dhaka and two are from outside of Dhaka. Three of them had contact with known patients tested for COVID-19, the source of one is unknown.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/news/two-doctors-among-four-new-cases-1886881|title=Two doctors among four new cases|date=2020-03-28|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/bengali/news-52059136|title=\u0986\u09b0\u09cb \u09ea \u099c\u09a8 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7, \u09a6\u09c1'\u099c\u09a8 \u099a\u09bf\u0995\u09bf\u09ce\u09b8\u0995|date=2020-03-27|work=BBC News \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be|access-date=2020-03-28|language=bn}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1647195/%E0%A6%A6%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%93-%E0%A6%9A%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%A1%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%B0|title=\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7 \u0986\u09b0\u0993 \u099a\u09be\u09b0\u099c\u09a8 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4: \u0986\u0987\u0987\u09a1\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u0986\u09b0|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref name=\":5\"/>\n*The government announced that in\u00a0addition to [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]], three other organizations have started testing for COVID-19. The institutions are Institute of Public Health(IPH), [[Dhaka Shishu Hospital]], and [[Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Diseases|Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Disease]] (BITID).<ref name=\"Research IEDCR\"/>\n* So far patients with suspected COVID-19 symptoms have been reported to have been assessed and died in [[Cox's Bazar]], [[Jessore]], [[Khagrachhari District|Khagrachhari]], [[Noakhali District|Noakhali]], [[Rajshahi]] etc.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangla.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/25/21533/%E0%A6%B9%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%AE-%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8B%E0%A7%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B7%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A6%82%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%8F%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%93|title=\u09b9\u09cb\u09ae \u0995\u09cb\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u099f\u09bf\u09a8\u09c7 \u09a8\u09be\u0987\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09cd\u09af\u0982\u099b\u09a1\u09bc\u09bf\u09b0 \u0987\u0989\u098f\u09a8\u0993|date=2020-03-25|website=Dhaka Tribune Bangla|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangla.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/25/21548/%E0%A6%96%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%97%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9B%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A5%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BE-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%97%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81,-%E0%A6%9A%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%8E%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%B9-%E0%A6%B9%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%AE-%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8B%E0%A7%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%9F%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%9A%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09c7\u09b0 \u0989\u09aa\u09b8\u09b0\u09cd\u0997 \u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0\u09b0 \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1, \u099a\u09bf\u0995\u09bf\u09ce\u09b8\u0995\u09b8\u09b9 \u09b9\u09cb\u09ae \u0995\u09cb\u09af\u09bc\u09be\u09b0\u09c7\u09a8\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u0987\u09a8\u09c7 \u099a\u09be\u09b0|date=2020-03-25|website=Dhaka Tribune Bangla|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bangla.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/25/21532/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%89%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%97-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%B6%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B9%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09c7\u09b0 \u0989\u09aa\u09b8\u09b0\u09cd\u0997 \u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09b0\u09be\u099c\u09b6\u09be\u09b9\u09c0\u09a4\u09c7 \u09a8\u09be\u09b0\u09c0\u09b0 \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1|date=2020-03-25|website=Dhaka Tribune Bangla|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n* Biman Bangladesh announced that it would suspend all domestic and international flights from March 30 till April 7. The airlines will operate its flights to London and Manchester on March 29 and fly back to Dhaka on March 30.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/news/biman-folds-its-wings-1886875|title=Biman folds its wings|date=2020-03-28|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*Despite lockdown, Muslims across the country were reported to have joined the [[Friday prayer|Jumah prayer]] at the mosques on Friday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/27/coronavirus-mosque-attendance-during-jumma-prayer-falls|title=Coronavirus: Mosque attendance during Jumma prayer falls|date=2020-03-27|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=\u0995\u09b2\u09cd\u09b2\u09cb\u09b2|first=\u0995\u09be\u09a6\u09bf\u09b0|url=https://www.bbc.com/bengali/news-52062149|title=\u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09b8\u099c\u09bf\u09a6\u0997\u09c1\u09b2\u09cb\u09af\u09bc \u099c\u09c1\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09be\u09b0 \u09ad\u09bf\u09a1\u09bc, \u09b8\u09b0\u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09bf \u0985\u09a8\u09c1\u09b0\u09cb\u09a7 \u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09be \u09b9\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7 \u09a8\u09be|date=2020-03-27|work=BBC News \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be|access-date=2020-03-28|language=bn}}</ref>\n*Bangladesh received medical supplies including 30,000 Covid-19 testing kits from [[Jack Ma]] Foundation founded by [[Alibaba Group|Alibaba]] Group's founder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/27/bangladesh-receives-medical-logistics-from-jack-ma-foundation|title=Bangladesh receives medical logistics from Jack Ma Foundation|date=2020-03-27|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/jack-ma-foundation-sends-30000-testing-kits-to-bangladesh|title=Jack Ma Foundation sends 30,000 testing kits to Bangladesh|website=Prothomalo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 28 ====\nOn March 28, it was reported that a total of 47 individuals were tested in the last 24 hours, but  none were newly tested positive. 4 new patients were declared as recovered from COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1647434/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%87-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%93-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%87|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09c7 \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987, \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1\u0993 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2020/03/28/no-new-coronavirus-cases-in-bangladesh-as-four-more-recover|title=No new coronavirus cases in Bangladesh as four more recover|last=Correspondent|first=Staff|last2=bdnews24.com|website=bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nTill date, there were a total of 1076 individuals tested among whom there were 48 known positive cases, 5 reported deaths, and 15 recoveries.\n\nHowever,  experts claim that a large number of people remain undetected due to inadequate testing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103274/coronavirus-fatality-rate-highest-in-bangladesh|title=Coronavirus fatality rate highest in Bangladesh|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 29 ====\nOn March 29, it was reported that 109 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, but none were tested positive. According to IEDCR, there were no new deaths from COVID-19 in the last 24 hours.These numbers consisted of tests conducted in [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]], Institute of Public Health(IPH), and [[Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Diseases|Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Disease]] (BITID).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jugantor.com/covid-19/293793/\u09e8\u09ea-\u0998\u09a3\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u09af\u09bc-\u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8-\u0995\u09b0\u09c7-\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be-\u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0-\u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4-\u09b9\u09af\u09bc\u09a8\u09bf-\u0986\u0987\u0987\u09a1\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u0986\u09b0|title=\u09e8\u09ea \u0998\u09a3\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u0995\u09b0\u09c7 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be \u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0 \u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09b9\u09af\u09bc\u09a8\u09bf: \u0986\u0987\u0987\u09a1\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u0986\u09b0|website=Jugantor|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n\nTill date, there were a total of 1095 individuals tested among whom were 48 known positive cases, 5 reported deaths, and 15 recoveries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/no-new-cases-detected-bangladesh-last-24hrs-iedcr-1887280|title=No new cases detected in Bangladesh in last 24hrs: IEDCR|date=2020-03-29|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n\nPatients with COVID-19 symptoms continued to die in hospitals without access to testing facilities in [[Barisal|Barishal]], [[Khulna]], [[Lalmonirhat]], [[Manikganj]], and [[Patuakhali]].  Some were treated at COVID-19 isolation centres at hospitals in the districts and others were denied treatment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103364/three-die-with-covid-19-symptoms-in-khulna-barishal-patuakhali|title=Three die with COVID-19 symptoms in Khulna, Barishal, Patuakhali|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref name=\"newagebd.net\"/>\n\n==== March 30 ====\nAccording to press briefing, 153 more tests were performed and one new COVID-19 positive case was identified in the past 24 hours. As of 30 March 2020, total number of COVID-19 positive cases in the country is 49.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://corona.gov.bd/storage/press-releases/March2020/Press%20Release%20COVID-19,%2030%20March%202020%20From%20Integrated%20Control%20Room%20DGHS.pdf|title=\u0995\u09cb\u09ad\u09bf\u09a1-\u09e7\u09ef \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7\u09b8 \u09b0\u09bf\u09b2\u09bf\u099c (\u09e9\u09e6-\u09e6\u09e9-\u09e8\u09e6\u09e8\u09e6)|website=corona.gov.bd|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n==== March 31 ====\nOn March 31, it was reported that 140 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, and two were tested positive. According to IEDCR, there were no new deaths from COVID-19 in the last 24 hours. These numbers consisted of tests conducted in [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]], [[Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Diseases|Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Disease]] (BITID), [[Dhaka Shishu Hospital]], [[International Centre for Diarrhoeal Disease Research, Bangladesh|icddr,b]], and [[Armed Forces Institute of Pathology, Bangladesh|AFIP]]. Till date, there were a total of 1602 individuals tested among whom were 51 known positive cases, 5 reported deaths, and 25 recoveries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://corona.gov.bd/storage/press-releases/March2020/Press%20Release%20COVID-19,%2031%20March%202020%20From%20Integrated%20Control%20Room%20DGHS.pdf|title=\u0995\u09cb\u09ad\u09bf\u09a1-\u09e7\u09ef \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7\u09b8 \u09b0\u09bf\u09b2\u09bf\u099c (\u09e9\u09e7-\u09e6\u09e9-\u09e8\u09e6\u09e8\u09e6)|website=corona.gov.bd|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nThe reality of low number of tests still remains as a concern among many in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/news/coronavirus-outbreak-low-test-rate-may-be-belying-reality-1888327|title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Low test rate may be belying reality|date=2020-04-01|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/bangla/\u09ae\u09a4\u09be\u09ae\u09a4/\u09e7-\u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u0993-\u09a8\u09af\u09bc-\u09e6\u09e7\u09ea-\u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0-\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be-\u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be-\u0993-\u09ae\u09c0\u09b0\u099c\u09be\u09a6\u09bf\u09b0-\u09a4\u09a5\u09cd\u09af-141799|title=\u09e7 \u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u0993 \u09a8\u09af\u09bc, \u09e6.\u09e7\u09ea \u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be \u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be \u0993 \u09ae\u09c0\u09b0\u099c\u09be\u09a6\u09bf\u09b0 \u09a4\u09a5\u09cd\u09af: \u0997\u09cb\u09b2\u09be\u09ae \u09ae\u09cb\u09b0\u09cd\u09a4\u09cb\u099c\u09be|date=2020-03-31|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020===\n\n==== April 1 ====\nThe Health Minister of Bangladesh said in a video call conference that one more COVID-19 patient had died and 3 more COVID-19 positive case was identified in the last 24 hours,This takes the number of deaths from Covid-19 to six and infected to 54 in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-update-in-bangladesh-1-more-dies-3-new-cases-confirmed-1888420|title=1 more dies of coronavirus, 3 new cases confirmed: health minister|date=2020-04-01|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==== April 2 ====\n\nOn April 2,it was reported that 141 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, and two were tested positive,both of them are male and one of them is 30-40 the other is between 70\u201380. According to [https://www.dghs.gov.bd/index.php/bd/ DGHS], there were no new deaths from COVID-19 in the last 24 hours.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-update-in-bangladesh-2-more-infected-1888798|title=Two more infected with coronavirus: DGHS|date=2020-04-02|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==== April 3 ====\nOn April 3,it was reported that 513 new samples were tested and among them 5 were tested positive in the last 24 hours,raising the total number of infected to 61.During this period no new death was reported across the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/04/03/coronavirus-5-more-infected-in-bangladesh-raising-total-to-61|title=Coronavirus: 5 more infected, no new death in 24hrs|date=2020-04-03|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n100 families in Narayanganj was put in self-isolation after a deceased woman was found Covid-19 positive last night.The IEDCR informed the district's civil surgeon around 7:00pm (April 2) last night that the woman was infected with coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/coronavirus-outbreak-100-nganj-families-put-self-isolation-1889134|title=Coronavirus outbreak: 100 N'ganj families put in self-isolation|date=2020-04-03|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==== April 4 ====\n\nOn April 4, it was reported that 434 samples were tested out of 553 new samples and among them 9 were tested positive in the last 24 hours, raising the total number of infected to 70. During this period, 2 new death was reported across the country which takes the number of deaths from Covid-19 to 8  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-death-in-bangladesh-total-8-died-1889446|title=Bangladesh reports 2 more coronavirus deaths|date=2020-04-04|website=The Daily Star|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==== April 5 ====\nOn April 5, it was reported that 367<ref>{{Citation|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u09e7\u09ee \u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8 \u098f\u09b2\u09be\u0995\u09be\u09b0 ? {{!}} Jamuna TV|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CYu0ZoS4i4E|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> new samples were tested and among them 18 were tested positive in the last 24 hours, raising the total number of infected to 88. During this period, 1 new death was reported across the country which takes the number of deaths from Covid-19 to 9.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2020/04/05/bangladesh-confirms-18-more-virus-cases-in-highest-single-day-spike|title=Bangladesh confirms 18 more virus cases in highest single-day spike|last=Correspondent|first=Senior|last2=bdnews24.com|website=bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Dhaka had 54 cases that time\n\n==== April 6 ====\nOn April 6, the country had '''the largest spike thus far''' in both the detected number of cases and the number of deaths, with '''35 new detected cases and 3 new deaths''' the number of positive tests surged from '''88 to 123''' and deaths increased from '''9 to 12'''.\n<ref>{{cite web|author=Star Online Report |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-in-bangladesh-reports-4-more-deaths-1890109 |title=Coronavirus in Bangladesh: Health Minister reports 4 more deaths |publisher=Thedailystar.net |date= |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>.It was the most cases of that time.At 2 pm IEDCR reports 127 cases.Bashabo in Dhaka was in a high risk.It was a lockdown.\n\nThe health authorities tested 468 samples to confirm the 35 new cases. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/health/coronavirus/2020/04/06/coronavirus-4-more-die-in-bangladesh-total-infected-117|title=Coronavirus: 3 more die in Bangladesh, total infected 123|date=2020-04-06|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==== April 7 ==== \nOn April 7, the country had the largest number of cases so far in both detected number of cases and the number of deaths, with '''41 new detected cases and 5 new deaths''' makes the number of positive case from 123 to 164 and deaths increased from 12 to 17<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-update-in-bangladesh-5-more-died-1890508|title=Bangladesh reports 5 more coronavirus deaths, 41 test positive in 24hrs: IEDCR}}</ref>\n\n==== April 8 ====\n'''3 more died''' of coronavirus infection in the last 24 hours, IEDCR said today. '''The death toll now stands at 20''', Dr. Meerjady Sabrina Flora, director, Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research (IEDCR) said during a briefing. '''54 people have tested positive''' for Covid-19 in last 24 hours. With this, '''the total number of infected has reached 218.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/bangladesh-reports-3-more-coronavirus-deaths-54-test-positive-24hrs-iedcr-1890868 |title=Bangladesh reports 3 more coronavirus deaths, 54 test positive in 24hrs: IEDCR|website=thedailystar.net |date= 8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe total number of tests conducted in last 24 hours were 981 among them 622 sample are collected from the capital<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/04/08/coronavirus-3-more-die-in-bangladesh|title=Coronavirus: 3 new deaths, 54 fresh cases, Dhaka now hotspot|date=2020-04-08|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==== April 9 ====\nOn April 9,  112 new people found positive and the death toll increased to 21. According to IEDCR, this is the biggest number of nCoV-19 positive found in a day so far. \n\nThe health authorities also stated that it tested 1,097 samples\u2014mostly from Dhaka--across the country, which the maximum in any given day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/health/coronavirus/2020/04/09/coronavirus-1-more-dies-new-infected-112|title=Coronavirus: Bangladesh reports 112 new cases as death toll climbs to 21|date=2020-04-09|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> \n\n==== April 10 ====\nAccording to MIS department of DGHS of Bangladesh, the death toll increased from 21 to 27 and the total detected case is 424.The health authorities also stated that it tested another record high of 1,184 samples in some 17 testing facilities across the country. Around 7,359 tests have been completed till now.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/health/coronavirus/2020/04/10/coronavirus-6-more-die-94-more-tested-positive|title=Coronavirus: 6 more die, 94 more test positive|date=2020-04-10|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==== April 13 ====\nThe death toll now stands at 39, the minister said during the briefing. One hundred and eighty-two people have tested positive for Covid-19 in the last 24 hours. With this, the total number of infected has reached 803. A total number of 1,570 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, the minister also said. Meanwhile three patients have recovered since yesterday taking the total recovery number to 42 so far, the minister added.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/five-more-coronavirus-patients-die-182-test-positive-24hrs-health-minister-1892539 |title=Five more coronavirus patients die, 182 test positive in 24hrs: health minister|date=2020-04-13|website=The Daily Star |access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n=== April 14 ===\n\n<br />\n\n==Testing and surveillance==\nOlder [[Rohingya refugees in Bangladesh|Rohingya refugees]] in overcrowded camps in Bangladesh are being left behind in [[humanitarian]] response to COVID-19, which could have devastating consequences given the high risks older people everywhere face from this deadly [[pandemic]], [[Amnesty International]] said.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/06/myanmar-bangladesh-older-people-denied-dignity-in-camps-after-facing-military-atrocities/|title=Myanmar/Bangladesh: Older people denied dignity in camps after facing military atrocities|website=[[Amnesty International]]|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Test related data\n!Total Sample Tested\n!13128\n|-\n| Tested per Million\n!80\n|-\n| Tested last 24hrs\n!1905\n|-\n! Total Positive\n! 1012\n|-\n| colspan=2| The above data was issued by the [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]], as of 13th April 2020.\n|}\n\n== Economic impact ==\n\nEven though garment factories were allowed to continue operating under the country's lockdown, an estimated one million garment workers, or one quarter of the workforce, were laid off due to declining orders for export.<ref>[https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/2020/04/03/826617334/1-million-bangladeshi-garment-workers-lose-jobs-amid-covid-19-economic-fallout 1 Million Bangladeshi Garment Workers Lose Jobs Amid COVID-19 Economic Fallout]</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 5 April, Prime Minister [[Sheikh Hasina]] announced a stimulus package amounting to some US$8bn.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2020/apr/05/bangladesh-announces-usd-8-billion-stimulus-package-to-fight-coronavirus-2126095.html|title=Bangladesh announces USD 8 billion stimulus package to fight coronavirus|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Cases in Bangladesh as reported by [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research (IEDCR]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://corona.gov.bd/press-release|title=Corona Info Press Release|last=|first=|date=|website=Corona Info|language=bn|url-status=live|access-date=}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=March 2020}}<!-- The data may come from sub-pages of the cited page, but each must be cited individually. The website will no longer exist in a few years, so it's also important to archive each individual link. -->\n!\n! colspan=\"4\" |\n! colspan=\"4\" |In the last 24 hours\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Notes\n|-\n!Date\n!Total Tested till 2020-04-13\n!Total Cases\n!Total Deaths\n!Total Recovered\n!Newly Tested\n!New Cases\n!New Deaths\n!Newly Recovered\n|-\n|2020-03-07\n|111<ref>{{cite web|url=https://matopath.com/2020/03/07/\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7-\u09af\u09c7\u0995\u09cb\u09a8\u09cb-\u09b8\u09ae\u09af\u09bc-\u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4-\u09b9\u09a4/|title=\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7 \u09af\u09c7\u0995\u09cb\u09a8\u09cb \u09b8\u09ae\u09af\u09bc \u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09b9\u09a4\u09c7 \u09aa\u09be\u09b0\u09c7 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be: \u0986\u0987\u0987\u09a1\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u0986\u09b0|last=newsupload|date=2020-03-07|website=\u09ae\u09a4 \u0993 \u09aa\u09a5|language=bn-BD|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-03-11\n|142<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bdnews24.com/health/2020/03/11/two-bangladeshi-patients-recover-from-coronavirus-infection-no-new-cases-detected-iedcr|title=Two Bangladeshi patients recover from coronavirus infection, no new cases detected: IEDCR|last=Correspondent|first=Staff|last2=bdnews24.com|website=bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n|3\n|0\n|2\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-03-12\n|163<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/current-affairs/2020/03/12/coronavirus-10-people-in-isolation-4-quarantined-in-bangladesh|title=Coronavirus: 10 people in isolation, 4 quarantined in Bangladesh|date=|work=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|3\n|0\n|2\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-02-13\n|187<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1644573/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%87-%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A5-%E0%A6%B9%E0%A7%9F%E0%A7%87-%E0%A7%A7-%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%BF.|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987, \u09b8\u09c1\u09b8\u09cd\u09a5 \u09b9\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09e7 \u099c\u09a8 \u09ac\u09be\u09a1\u09bc\u09bf \u09ab\u09bf\u09b0\u09c7\u099b\u09c7\u09a8|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n|3\n|0\n|2\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-03-14\n|211<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/dhaka/2020/03/14/iedcr-3rd-coronavirus-patient-now-tests-negative.|title=No coronavirus patients in Bangladesh now|date=|work=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|5\n|0\n|3\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-03-15\n|231<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/world/story/coronavirus-outbreak-confirmed-cases-bangladesh-quarantined-isolation-1655755-2020-03-15|title