9\u09aa\u09b8\u09b0\u09cd\u0997 \u09a8\u09bf\u09af\u09bc\u09c7 \u09b0\u09be\u099c\u09b6\u09be\u09b9\u09c0\u09a4\u09c7 \u09a8\u09be\u09b0\u09c0\u09b0 \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1|date=2020-03-25|website=Dhaka Tribune Bangla|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n* Biman Bangladesh announced that it would suspend all domestic and international flights from March 30 till April 7. The airlines will operate its flights to London and Manchester on March 29 and fly back to Dhaka on March 30.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/news/biman-folds-its-wings-1886875|title=Biman folds its wings|date=2020-03-28|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n*Despite lockdown, Muslims across the country were reported to have joined the [[Friday prayer|Jumah prayer]] at the mosques on Friday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/27/coronavirus-mosque-attendance-during-jumma-prayer-falls|title=Coronavirus: Mosque attendance during Jumma prayer falls|date=2020-03-27|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=\u0995\u09b2\u09cd\u09b2\u09cb\u09b2|first=\u0995\u09be\u09a6\u09bf\u09b0|url=https://www.bbc.com/bengali/news-52062149|title=\u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09b8\u099c\u09bf\u09a6\u0997\u09c1\u09b2\u09cb\u09af\u09bc \u099c\u09c1\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09be\u09b0 \u09ad\u09bf\u09a1\u09bc, \u09b8\u09b0\u0995\u09be\u09b0\u09bf \u0985\u09a8\u09c1\u09b0\u09cb\u09a7 \u09ae\u09be\u09a8\u09be \u09b9\u099a\u09cd\u099b\u09c7 \u09a8\u09be|date=2020-03-27|work=BBC News \u09ac\u09be\u0982\u09b2\u09be|access-date=2020-03-28|language=bn}}</ref>\n*Bangladesh received medical supplies including 30,000 Covid-19 testing kits from [[Jack Ma]] Foundation founded by [[Alibaba Group|Alibaba]] Group's founder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/03/27/bangladesh-receives-medical-logistics-from-jack-ma-foundation|title=Bangladesh receives medical logistics from Jack Ma Foundation|date=2020-03-27|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/jack-ma-foundation-sends-30000-testing-kits-to-bangladesh|title=Jack Ma Foundation sends 30,000 testing kits to Bangladesh|website=Prothomalo|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 28 ====\nOn March 28, it was reported that a total of 47 individuals were tested in the last 24 hours, but  none were newly tested positive. 4 new patients were declared as recovered from COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1647434/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%AD%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%87%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%87-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%87-%E0%A6%AE%E0%A7%83%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%AF%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%93-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%87|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09ad\u09be\u0987\u09b0\u09be\u09b8\u09c7 \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987, \u09ae\u09c3\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09c1\u0993 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987|website=\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09a5\u09ae \u0986\u09b2\u09cb|language=bn|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2020/03/28/no-new-coronavirus-cases-in-bangladesh-as-four-more-recover|title=No new coronavirus cases in Bangladesh as four more recover|last=Correspondent|first=Staff|last2=bdnews24.com|website=bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\nTill date, there were a total of 1076 individuals tested among whom there were 48 known positive cases, 5 reported deaths, and 15 recoveries.\n\nHowever,  experts claim that a large number of people remain undetected due to inadequate testing.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103274/coronavirus-fatality-rate-highest-in-bangladesh|title=Coronavirus fatality rate highest in Bangladesh|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n==== March 29 ====\nOn March 29, it was reported that 109 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, but none were tested positive. According to IEDCR, there were no new deaths from COVID-19 in the last 24 hours.These numbers consisted of tests conducted in [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]], Institute of Public Health(IPH), and [[Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Diseases|Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Disease]] (BITID).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jugantor.com/covid-19/293793/\u09e8\u09ea-\u0998\u09a3\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u09af\u09bc-\u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8-\u0995\u09b0\u09c7-\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be-\u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0-\u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4-\u09b9\u09af\u09bc\u09a8\u09bf-\u0986\u0987\u0987\u09a1\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u0986\u09b0|title=\u09e8\u09ea \u0998\u09a3\u09cd\u099f\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u0995\u09b0\u09c7 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be \u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0 \u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09b9\u09af\u09bc\u09a8\u09bf: \u0986\u0987\u0987\u09a1\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u0986\u09b0|website=Jugantor|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n\nTill date, there were a total of 1095 individuals tested among whom were 48 known positive cases, 5 reported deaths, and 15 recoveries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/no-new-cases-detected-bangladesh-last-24hrs-iedcr-1887280|title=No new cases detected in Bangladesh in last 24hrs: IEDCR|date=2020-03-29|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n\nPatients with COVID-19 symptoms continued to die in hospitals without access to testing facilities in [[Barisal|Barishal]], [[Khulna]], [[Lalmonirhat]], [[Manikganj]], and [[Patuakhali]].  Some were treated at COVID-19 isolation centres at hospitals in the districts and others were denied treatment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newagebd.net/article/103364/three-die-with-covid-19-symptoms-in-khulna-barishal-patuakhali|title=Three die with COVID-19 symptoms in Khulna, Barishal, Patuakhali|website=New Age {{!}} The Most Popular Outspoken English Daily in Bangladesh|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref name=\"newagebd.net\"/>\n\n==== March 30 ====\nAccording to press briefing, 153 more tests were performed and one new COVID-19 positive case was identified in the past 24 hours. As of 30 March 2020, total number of COVID-19 positive cases in the country is 49.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://corona.gov.bd/storage/press-releases/March2020/Press%20Release%20COVID-19,%2030%20March%202020%20From%20Integrated%20Control%20Room%20DGHS.pdf|title=\u0995\u09cb\u09ad\u09bf\u09a1-\u09e7\u09ef \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7\u09b8 \u09b0\u09bf\u09b2\u09bf\u099c (\u09e9\u09e6-\u09e6\u09e9-\u09e8\u09e6\u09e8\u09e6)|website=corona.gov.bd|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n==== March 31 ====\nOn March 31, it was reported that 140 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, and two were tested positive. According to IEDCR, there were no new deaths from COVID-19 in the last 24 hours. These numbers consisted of tests conducted in [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]], [[Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Diseases|Bangladesh Institute of Tropical and Infectious Disease]] (BITID), [[Dhaka Shishu Hospital]], [[International Centre for Diarrhoeal Disease Research, Bangladesh|icddr,b]], and [[Armed Forces Institute of Pathology, Bangladesh|AFIP]]. Till date, there were a total of 1602 individuals tested among whom were 51 known positive cases, 5 reported deaths, and 25 recoveries.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://corona.gov.bd/storage/press-releases/March2020/Press%20Release%20COVID-19,%2031%20March%202020%20From%20Integrated%20Control%20Room%20DGHS.pdf|title=\u0995\u09cb\u09ad\u09bf\u09a1-\u09e7\u09ef \u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09c7\u09b8 \u09b0\u09bf\u09b2\u09bf\u099c (\u09e9\u09e7-\u09e6\u09e9-\u09e8\u09e6\u09e8\u09e6)|website=corona.gov.bd|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nThe reality of low number of tests still remains as a concern among many in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/news/coronavirus-outbreak-low-test-rate-may-be-belying-reality-1888327|title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Low test rate may be belying reality|date=2020-04-01|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/bangla/\u09ae\u09a4\u09be\u09ae\u09a4/\u09e7-\u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u0993-\u09a8\u09af\u09bc-\u09e6\u09e7\u09ea-\u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0-\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be-\u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be-\u0993-\u09ae\u09c0\u09b0\u099c\u09be\u09a6\u09bf\u09b0-\u09a4\u09a5\u09cd\u09af-141799|title=\u09e7 \u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u0993 \u09a8\u09af\u09bc, \u09e6.\u09e7\u09ea \u09b6\u09a4\u09be\u0982\u09b6\u09c7\u09b0 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be \u09aa\u09b0\u09c0\u0995\u09cd\u09b7\u09be \u0993 \u09ae\u09c0\u09b0\u099c\u09be\u09a6\u09bf\u09b0 \u09a4\u09a5\u09cd\u09af: \u0997\u09cb\u09b2\u09be\u09ae \u09ae\u09cb\u09b0\u09cd\u09a4\u09cb\u099c\u09be|date=2020-03-31|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020===\n\n==== April 1 ====\nThe Health Minister of Bangladesh said in a video call conference that one more COVID-19 patient had died and 3 more COVID-19 positive case was identified in the last 24 hours,This takes the number of deaths from Covid-19 to six and infected to 54 in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-update-in-bangladesh-1-more-dies-3-new-cases-confirmed-1888420|title=1 more dies of coronavirus, 3 new cases confirmed: health minister|date=2020-04-01|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==== April 2 ====\n\nOn April 2,it was reported that 141 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, and two were tested positive,both of them are male and one of them is 30-40 the other is between 70\u201380. According to [https://www.dghs.gov.bd/index.php/bd/ DGHS], there were no new deaths from COVID-19 in the last 24 hours.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-update-in-bangladesh-2-more-infected-1888798|title=Two more infected with coronavirus: DGHS|date=2020-04-02|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==== April 3 ====\nOn April 3,it was reported that 513 new samples were tested and among them 5 were tested positive in the last 24 hours,raising the total number of infected to 61.During this period no new death was reported across the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/04/03/coronavirus-5-more-infected-in-bangladesh-raising-total-to-61|title=Coronavirus: 5 more infected, no new death in 24hrs|date=2020-04-03|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n100 families in Narayanganj was put in self-isolation after a deceased woman was found Covid-19 positive last night.The IEDCR informed the district's civil surgeon around 7:00pm (April 2) last night that the woman was infected with coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/coronavirus-outbreak-100-nganj-families-put-self-isolation-1889134|title=Coronavirus outbreak: 100 N'ganj families put in self-isolation|date=2020-04-03|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n\n==== April 4 ====\n\nOn April 4, it was reported that 434 samples were tested out of 553 new samples and among them 9 were tested positive in the last 24 hours, raising the total number of infected to 70. During this period, 2 new death was reported across the country which takes the number of deaths from Covid-19 to 8  <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-death-in-bangladesh-total-8-died-1889446|title=Bangladesh reports 2 more coronavirus deaths|date=2020-04-04|website=The Daily Star|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==== April 5 ====\nOn April 5, it was reported that 367<ref>{{Citation|title=\u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be\u09af\u09bc \u0986\u0995\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a4 \u09a8\u09a4\u09c1\u09a8 \u09e7\u09ee \u09b0\u09cb\u0997\u09c0 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8 \u0995\u09cb\u09a8 \u098f\u09b2\u09be\u0995\u09be\u09b0 ? {{!}} Jamuna TV|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CYu0ZoS4i4E|language=en|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> new samples were tested and among them 18 were tested positive in the last 24 hours, raising the total number of infected to 88. During this period, 1 new death was reported across the country which takes the number of deaths from Covid-19 to 9.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2020/04/05/bangladesh-confirms-18-more-virus-cases-in-highest-single-day-spike|title=Bangladesh confirms 18 more virus cases in highest single-day spike|last=Correspondent|first=Senior|last2=bdnews24.com|website=bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref> Dhaka had 54 cases that time\n\n==== April 6 ====\nOn April 6, the country had '''the largest spike thus far''' in both the detected number of cases and the number of deaths, with '''35 new detected cases and 3 new deaths''' the number of positive tests surged from '''88 to 123''' and deaths increased from '''9 to 12'''.\n<ref>{{cite web|author=Star Online Report |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-in-bangladesh-reports-4-more-deaths-1890109 |title=Coronavirus in Bangladesh: Health Minister reports 4 more deaths |publisher=Thedailystar.net |date= |accessdate=2020-04-07}}</ref>.It was the most cases of that time.At 2 pm IEDCR reports 127 cases.Bashabo in Dhaka was in a high risk.It was a lockdown.\n\nThe health authorities tested 468 samples to confirm the 35 new cases. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/health/coronavirus/2020/04/06/coronavirus-4-more-die-in-bangladesh-total-infected-117|title=Coronavirus: 3 more die in Bangladesh, total infected 123|date=2020-04-06|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==== April 7 ==== \nOn April 7, the country had the largest number of cases so far in both detected number of cases and the number of deaths, with '''41 new detected cases and 5 new deaths''' makes the number of positive case from 123 to 164 and deaths increased from 12 to 17<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-update-in-bangladesh-5-more-died-1890508|title=Bangladesh reports 5 more coronavirus deaths, 41 test positive in 24hrs: IEDCR}}</ref>\n\n==== April 8 ====\n'''3 more died''' of coronavirus infection in the last 24 hours, IEDCR said today. '''The death toll now stands at 20''', Dr. Meerjady Sabrina Flora, director, Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research (IEDCR) said during a briefing. '''54 people have tested positive''' for Covid-19 in last 24 hours. With this, '''the total number of infected has reached 218.'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/bangladesh-reports-3-more-coronavirus-deaths-54-test-positive-24hrs-iedcr-1890868 |title=Bangladesh reports 3 more coronavirus deaths, 54 test positive in 24hrs: IEDCR|website=thedailystar.net |date= 8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe total number of tests conducted in last 24 hours were 981 among them 622 sample are collected from the capital<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/2020/04/08/coronavirus-3-more-die-in-bangladesh|title=Coronavirus: 3 new deaths, 54 fresh cases, Dhaka now hotspot|date=2020-04-08|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==== April 9 ====\nOn April 9,  112 new people found positive and the death toll increased to 21. According to IEDCR, this is the biggest number of nCoV-19 positive found in a day so far. \n\nThe health authorities also stated that it tested 1,097 samples\u2014mostly from Dhaka--across the country, which the maximum in any given day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/health/coronavirus/2020/04/09/coronavirus-1-more-dies-new-infected-112|title=Coronavirus: Bangladesh reports 112 new cases as death toll climbs to 21|date=2020-04-09|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> \n\n==== April 10 ====\nAccording to MIS department of DGHS of Bangladesh, the death toll increased from 21 to 27 and the total detected case is 424.The health authorities also stated that it tested another record high of 1,184 samples in some 17 testing facilities across the country. Around 7,359 tests have been completed till now.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/health/coronavirus/2020/04/10/coronavirus-6-more-die-94-more-tested-positive|title=Coronavirus: 6 more die, 94 more test positive|date=2020-04-10|website=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref>\n\n==== April 13 ====\nThe death toll now stands at 39, the minister said during the briefing. One hundred and eighty-two people have tested positive for Covid-19 in the last 24 hours. With this, the total number of infected has reached 803. A total number of 1,570 samples were tested in the last 24 hours, the minister also said. Meanwhile three patients have recovered since yesterday taking the total recovery number to 42 so far, the minister added.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/coronavirus-deadly-new-threat/news/five-more-coronavirus-patients-die-182-test-positive-24hrs-health-minister-1892539 |title=Five more coronavirus patients die, 182 test positive in 24hrs: health minister|date=2020-04-13|website=The Daily Star |access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n=== April 14 ===\n\n<br />\n\n==Testing and surveillance==\nOlder [[Rohingya refugees in Bangladesh|Rohingya refugees]] in overcrowded camps in Bangladesh are being left behind in [[humanitarian]] response to COVID-19, which could have devastating consequences given the high risks older people everywhere face from this deadly [[pandemic]], [[Amnesty International]] said.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2019/06/myanmar-bangladesh-older-people-denied-dignity-in-camps-after-facing-military-atrocities/|title=Myanmar/Bangladesh: Older people denied dignity in camps after facing military atrocities|website=[[Amnesty International]]|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Test related data\n!Total Sample Tested\n!13128\n|-\n| Tested per Million\n!80\n|-\n| Tested last 24hrs\n!1905\n|-\n! Total Positive\n! 1012\n|-\n| colspan=2| The above data was issued by the [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|IEDCR]], as of 13th April 2020.\n|}\n\n== Economic impact ==\n\nEven though garment factories were allowed to continue operating under the country's lockdown, an estimated one million garment workers, or one quarter of the workforce, were laid off due to declining orders for export.<ref>[https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/2020/04/03/826617334/1-million-bangladeshi-garment-workers-lose-jobs-amid-covid-19-economic-fallout 1 Million Bangladeshi Garment Workers Lose Jobs Amid COVID-19 Economic Fallout]</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\nOn 5 April, Prime Minister [[Sheikh Hasina]] announced a stimulus package amounting to some US$8bn.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2020/apr/05/bangladesh-announces-usd-8-billion-stimulus-package-to-fight-coronavirus-2126095.html|title=Bangladesh announces USD 8 billion stimulus package to fight coronavirus|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-04-06}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Cases in Bangladesh as reported by [[Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research|Institute of Epidemiology, Disease Control and Research (IEDCR]]) <ref>{{cite web|url=https://corona.gov.bd/press-release|title=Corona Info Press Release|last=|first=|date=|website=Corona Info|language=bn|url-status=live|access-date=}}</ref>{{failed verification|date=March 2020}}<!-- The data may come from sub-pages of the cited page, but each must be cited individually. The website will no longer exist in a few years, so it's also important to archive each individual link. -->\n!\n! colspan=\"4\" |\n! colspan=\"4\" |In the last 24 hours\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Notes\n|-\n!Date\n!Total Tested till 2020-04-13\n!Total Cases\n!Total Deaths\n!Total Recovered\n!Newly Tested\n!New Cases\n!New Deaths\n!Newly Recovered\n|-\n|2020-03-07\n|111<ref>{{cite web|url=https://matopath.com/2020/03/07/\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7-\u09af\u09c7\u0995\u09cb\u09a8\u09cb-\u09b8\u09ae\u09af\u09bc-\u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4-\u09b9\u09a4/|title=\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6\u09c7 \u09af\u09c7\u0995\u09cb\u09a8\u09cb \u09b8\u09ae\u09af\u09bc \u09b6\u09a8\u09be\u0995\u09cd\u09a4 \u09b9\u09a4\u09c7 \u09aa\u09be\u09b0\u09c7 \u0995\u09b0\u09cb\u09a8\u09be: \u0986\u0987\u0987\u09a1\u09bf\u09b8\u09bf\u0986\u09b0|last=newsupload|date=2020-03-07|website=\u09ae\u09a4 \u0993 \u09aa\u09a5|language=bn-BD|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n|0\n|0\n|0\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-03-11\n|142<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bdnews24.com/health/2020/03/11/two-bangladeshi-patients-recover-from-coronavirus-infection-no-new-cases-detected-iedcr|title=Two Bangladeshi patients recover from coronavirus infection, no new cases detected: IEDCR|last=Correspondent|first=Staff|last2=bdnews24.com|website=bdnews24.com|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n|3\n|0\n|2\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-03-12\n|163<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/current-affairs/2020/03/12/coronavirus-10-people-in-isolation-4-quarantined-in-bangladesh|title=Coronavirus: 10 people in isolation, 4 quarantined in Bangladesh|date=|work=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|3\n|0\n|2\n|\n|\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|2020-02-13\n|187<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/1644573/%E0%A6%95%E0%A6%B0%E0%A7%8B%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%BE%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8-%E0%A6%86%E0%A6%95%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BE%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%8D%E0